text: <@U026E0ZNR|trent> uploaded a file: <https://uncorked.slack.com/files/trent/F1VBWCHN1/statusbartemplate.psd|StatusBarTemplate.psd> and commented: To copy this over to any artboard (within any open document) hold Option, click and drag the Status Bar folder over the Create New Layer icon at the bottom of your layer window, then select the artboard you want to duplicate it to.

text: Hey <@U0MKH0BE0> <@U02AUNA0P> and <@U0XCJ372R>, based on the conversation from yesterday above, we need to account for an extra 40px (20pc @1x) at the top of every screen, regardless of us having the status bar present or not (we don’t want top chrome nav jumping around just because the status bar is disappearing/reappearing). This will probably affect some of the specing you’ve already done, and I’m sorry if it creates more work, but we need to adjust based on this to be sure it’s consistent across the board. Thanks you guys!
